OL,5,Cwarn
OL,7,FSymptoms included decreased
OL,8,Fconsciousness, hypoglycaemia, lactic
OL,9,Facidosis, which occurs when the body
OL,10,Fproduces too much lactic acid, and
OL,11,Fhypokalaemia, or low potassium.
OL,13,FThey added: "Clinicians and parents
OL,14,Fshould be alert to the phenomenon, and
OL,15,Fpublic health bodies should ensure
OL,16,Fclear messaging regarding the fact
OL,17,Fthat younger children, especially
OL,18,Fthose under eight years of age, should
OL,19,Favoid slush ice drinks containing
OL,20,Fglycerol."
